This paper deals with local feature extraction and matching, which is a common task in computer vision. The paper evaluates the performance of various transformation estimation techniques on different datasets and synthetic correspondences. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with 3D registration and modeling, which are tasks commonly associated with Robotics (cs.RO) and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the efficiency of the methods, which suggests that it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
